  "text": "The Kubernetes CSI driver integration is implemented across multiple components in kubernetes/kubernetes:\n\n## CSI Node Plugin Client\nThe `pkg/volume/csi/csi_client.go` file implements the CSI node plugin client as a gRPC client. It defines the `csiClient` interface and `csiDriverClient` struct which communicates with CSI drivers running on nodes. This client handles node operations like NodeGetInfo, NodePublishVolume, NodeStageVolume, NodeUnpublishVolume, and NodeExpandVolume.\n\n## CSI Volume Plugin\nThe `pkg/volume/csi/csi_plugin.go` file implements the main CSI volume plugin, which registers with Kubernetes' volume plugin system. The `csiPlugin` struct implements the VolumePlugin interface and provides factory methods for creating attachers, mounters, and block mappers. The `ProbeVolumePlugins()` function serves as the entry point for registering the CSI plugin.\n\n## CSI Volume Attach/Detach Controller\nThe `pkg/volume/csi/csi_attacher.go` file implements volume attachment and detachment for CSI volumes. The `csiAttacher` struct implements the Attacher, Detacher, and DeviceMounter interfaces. It creates VolumeAttachment objects and monitors their status for CSI attach/detach operations.\n\n## CSI Mounter and Block Volume Support\nThe `pkg/volume/csi/csi_mounter.go` and `pkg/volume/csi/csi_block.go` files handle volume mounting and block volume operations respectively. The `csiMounter` handles filesystem volumes while `csiBlockMapper` handles block volumes, both using the CSI client to stage and publish volumes.\n\n## Node Information Manager\nThe `pkg/volume/csi/nodeinfomanager/nodeinfomanager.go` file manages CSI node topology information, tracking node capabilities and volume limits reported by CSI drivers.\n\n## PersistentVolume Controller\nThe `pkg/controller/volume/persistentvolume/pv_controller.go` and `pv_controller_base.go` files implement the PersistentVolume controller that bridges CSI operations to the core storage API. The `PersistentVolumeController` manages PV provisioning, binding, and deletion. The `provisionClaimOperationExternal` method handles external provisioning including CSI drivers. It translates in-tree provisioner names to CSI names using the CSI translation library when CSI migration is enabled.\n\n## Attach/Detach Controller\nThe `pkg/controller/volume/attachdetach/attach_detach_controller.go` file implements the attach/detach controller which orchestrates volume attachment operations across nodes. It uses CSI migration support and the CSI translation library to handle both native CSI and migrated in-tree volumes.\n\n## Volume Expansion Controller\nThe `pkg/controller/volume/expand/expand_controller.go` file handles volume expansion, including CSI-based volume resizing. It detects when CSI migration is enabled and coordinates with external CSI resizers.\n\n## CSI Migration Support\nThe `pkg/volume/csimigration/plugin_manager.go` file implements CSI migration plugin management, allowing in-tree volume plugins to be transparently migrated to their CSI equivalents.\n\n## Scheduler Plugin\nThe `pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/nodevolumelimits/csi.go` file implements scheduler filtering based on CSI node volume limits, preventing pods from being scheduled on nodes that exceed their CSI volume attachment limits.\n\n## CSI Translation Library\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/csi-translation-lib/` directory contains the CSI translation library which:\n- `translate.go`: Main translation utilities that convert between in-tree volume specs and CSI specifications\n- `plugins/in_tree_volume.go`: Base translation interface\n- `plugins/{aws_ebs,gce_pd,azure_disk,azure_file,vsphere_volume,openstack_cinder,portworx}.go`: Plugin-specific translations for migrating in-tree drivers to CSI\n- `plugins/const.go`: Translation constants\n\nThese components work together to provide a complete CSI driver integration in Kubernetes, allowing CSI drivers to manage volumes while maintaining compatibility with the core storage subsystem through the PersistentVolume API."
}

